ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000Fehwr:ref

Hi Pasan

Just seeing if we have an update to our problem in our test environment post running FS_MigrateSchema?  As you recall the job encountered an error on 13.Migrate DLP MatchHits: "Could not drop object 'SA_FSDLP_MatchHits' because it is referenced by a FOREIGN KEY constraint."
After this everything is working as expected other than the FSAA Imports job where we see these errors: "Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_gatesproxyid_idx'.  Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_rightsproxyid_idx'.  Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_parentresourceid_name_idx'.  Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_enum_idx'."
I had taken a backup of the DB before I ran FS_MigrateSchema so I need Netwrix to advise if I should restore the DB or whether we can work through this problem?

Regards

Mark Chambers
Infrastructure Operations Senior Specialist
Workplace Services and Contact Centre Platforms

Hi team

The FS_MigrateSchema job has finished running in my test environment and I am validating the functionality of the application and I am encountering some problems:

  1.  FS_MigrateSchema encountered an error with 13.Migrate DLP MatchHits.  Error message is "Could not drop object 'SA_FSDLP_MatchHits' because it is referenced by a FOREIGN KEY constraint."  It appears that 'SA_FSDLP_MatchHits' table is used by Sensitive Data which we don't use.  Is this going to impact anything else?  How can it be fixed?
  2.  When running an FSAA import job I encountered the following error:
Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_gatesproxyid_idx'.
Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_rightsproxyid_idx'.
Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_parentresourceid_name_idx'.
Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_enum_idx'.

Why is this a problem and how can this be fixed?

Just to reiterate the context, I am running FS_MigrateSchema  to fix an issue with the FileSystemOverview in our production environment.  I am running this in test to see how environment reacts before running the same job in production.  Unless these issues can be fixed I will be unable to run this job in production which will impact the running of FileSystemOverview which we use to track our open shares.

The change window I am operating under expires tomorrow.  I have taken a backup of the DB, if we cannot fix these issues I will ask for the DB to be restored, does anything else need to be run to undo what FS_MigrateSchema has done?

Regards

Mark Chambers
Infrastructure Operations Senior Specialist
Workplace Services and Contact Centre Platforms

Hi Mark

My apologies for delay in reply.

1. If are running this against a seperate database (i.e. test has independent db) then this is not a problem, it should give an indication of time to run.
2. Default is inheriting the host list from above, however this job is a list of SQL scripts which do not reference host list, therefore this setting is not relevant and can be left as default.
3. If this has run successfully, the Status | TaskStats should show as "success" for all the scripts. We can also run sp_help against the FSAA tables to verify the data type for the ID value. If you need assistance with this we can provide steps.


Thank you,

Hi team

The FS_MigrateSchema job has finished running in my test environment and I am validating the functionality of the application and I am encountering some problems:

  1.  FS_MigrateSchema encountered an error with 13.Migrate DLP MatchHits.  Error message is "Could not drop object 'SA_FSDLP_MatchHits' because it is referenced by a FOREIGN KEY constraint."  It appears that 'SA_FSDLP_MatchHits' table is used by Sensitive Data which we don't use.  Is this going to impact anything else?  How can it be fixed?
  2.  When running an FSAA import job I encountered the following error:
Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_gatesproxyid_idx'.
Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_rightsproxyid_idx'.
Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_parentresourceid_name_idx'.
Cannot find index 'sa_fsaa_resources_enum_idx'.

Why is this a problem and how can this be fixed?

Just to reiterate the context, I am running FS_MigrateSchema  to fix an issue with the FileSystemOverview in our production environment.  I am running this in test to see how environment reacts before running the same job in production.  Unless these issues can be fixed I will be unable to run this job in production which will impact the running of FileSystemOverview which we use to track our open shares.

The change window I am operating under expires tomorrow.  I have taken a backup of the DB, if we cannot fix these issues I will ask for the DB to be restored, does anything else need to be run to undo what FS_MigrateSchema has done?

Regards
